{"parse":{"title":"Joseph Fielding Smith Institute for Church History","pageid":19852879,"revid":807940187,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about a history organization. For the UK charity and think tank, see <a href=\"/wiki/Smith_Institute\" title=\"Smith Institute\">Smith Institute</a>.</div>\n<p>The <b>Joseph Fielding Smith Institute for Church History</b> (later renamed to <b>Joseph Fielding Smith Institute for Latter-day Saint History</b>) was an academic research organization at <a href=\"/wiki/Brigham_Young_University\" title=\"Brigham Young University\">Brigham Young University</a> (BYU) from 1980 to 2005 that sought to promote the study of the history of <a href=\"/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints\" title=\"The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints\">The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MH_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MH-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Controversies\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Controversies</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Fielding_Smith_Institute_for_Church_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1982, the History Division of the church's Historical Department was dissolved and its staff transferred to BYU, to become part of the Smith Institute. <a href=\"/wiki/Leonard_J._Arrington\" title=\"Leonard J. Arrington\">Leonard J. Arrington</a>, who headed the History Division from 1972\u20131982, also led the Smith Institute from 1980-1986.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MH_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MH-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Arrington was succeeded as head of the institute by <a href=\"/wiki/Ron_Esplin\" title=\"Ron Esplin\">Ron Esplin</a>.  Esplin was succeeded by <a href=\"/wiki/Jill_Mulvay_Derr\" title=\"Jill Mulvay Derr\">Jill Mulvay Derr</a>.\n</p><p>The Smith Institute operated as part of <a href=\"/wiki/BYU%27s_College_of_Family,_Home_and_Social_Sciences\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"BYU&#39;s College of Family, Home and Social Sciences\">BYU's College of Family, Home and Social Sciences</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2005, with the growth of the <a href=\"/wiki/Joseph_Smith_Papers_Project\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Joseph Smith Papers Project\">Joseph Smith Papers Project</a>, and with its relocation to the <a href=\"/wiki/Church_Historian_and_Recorder\" title=\"Church Historian and Recorder\">Family and Church History Department</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Salt_Lake_City\" title=\"Salt Lake City\">Salt Lake City</a>, it was decided to dissolve the institute and have various academic departments at BYU continue research in church history topics.  Some of the former faculty members of the institute, such as <a href=\"/wiki/Grant_Underwood\" title=\"Grant Underwood\">Grant Underwood</a> were transferred to BYU's history department.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Controversies\">Controversies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Fielding_Smith_Institute_for_Church_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Controversies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2003 in response to <a href=\"/wiki/Grant_Palmer\" title=\"Grant Palmer\">Grant Palmer</a>'s book in which he gave the impression that at least some of the scholars at the Joseph Fielding Smith Institute supported his views on church history, the Smith Institute issued a statement directly rejecting the views advanced by Palmer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify\" title=\"Wikipedia:Please clarify\"><span title=\"The text near this tag may need clarification or removal of jargon. (January 2013)\">clarification needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Fielding_Smith_Institute_for_Church_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-MH-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-MH_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-MH_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Ronald_W._Walker\" title=\"Ronald W. Walker\">Walker, Ronald W.</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/David_J._Whittaker\" title=\"David J. Whittaker\">David J. Whittaker</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/James_B._Allen_(historian)\" title=\"James B. Allen (historian)\">James B. Allen</a> (2001). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/?id=-iSVA0KRs4MC&amp;printsec=frontcover#PPA68,M1\"><i>Mormon History</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Urbana,_Illinois\" title=\"Urbana, Illinois\">Urbana</a>: <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press\" title=\"University of Illinois Press\">University of Illinois Press</a>. p.&#160;68. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-252-02619-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-252-02619-5\">0-252-02619-5</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-10-21</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+History&amp;rft.place=Urbana&amp;rft.pages=68&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.isbn=0-252-02619-5&amp;rft.au=Walker%2C+Ronald+W.&amp;rft.au=David+J.+Whittaker&amp;rft.au=James+B.+Allen&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2F%3Fid%3D-iSVA0KRs4MC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%23PPA68%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Fielding+Smith+Institute+for+Church+History\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://saas.byu.edu/catalog/archive/1998/info/colleges/Family.html\">1998-1999 BYU catalogue</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20081006123420/http://saas.byu.edu/catalog/archive/1998/info/colleges/family.html\">Archived</a> 2008-10-06 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://farms.byu.edu/publications/review/?vol=15&amp;num=2&amp;id=510\">text of Smith Institute statement</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Joseph_Fielding_Smith_Institute_for_Church_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Searle, Howard C. (1992). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://eom.byu.edu/index.php/Historians%2C_Church\">\"Historians, Church\"</a>.  In <a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_H._Ludlow\" title=\"Daniel H. Ludlow\">Ludlow, Daniel</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Encyclopedia_of_Mormonism\" title=\"Encyclopedia of Mormonism\">Encyclopedia of Mormonism</a></i>. <a href=\"/wiki/Macmillan_Publishers\" title=\"Macmillan Publishers\">Macmillan</a>. pp.&#160;591\u2013592.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Historians%2C+Church&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.pages=591-592&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.aulast=Searle&amp;rft.aufirst=Howard+C.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Feom.byu.edu%2Findex.php%2FHistorians%252C_Church&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Fielding+Smith+Institute+for+Church+History\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20040810200412/http://smithinstitute.byu.e